:"Without cleaning mixing bowl, place onion and remaining oil into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Add bacon and cook <b>8 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>, <strong>without measuring cup<\/strong>. Allow mixture to cool in mixing bowl for 10 minutes."},{"content":"Preheat oven to 200°C. Set aside a ceramic or glass baking dish (23 x 30 cm)."},{"content":"Add cream cheese, egg, nutmeg, reserved zucchini flesh and 50 g of the reserved grated cheese to mixing bowl and combine <b>10 sec\/\/speed 2<b>. Place reserved zucchini skins into baking dish and fill with cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle with remaining grated cheese and bake for 20 minutes (200°C) or until golden brown. Serve immediately."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Emmental cheese can be replaced with Swiss cheese."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 5m","6 portions"]}